{"declarations":[{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/Tactic/Linter/Whitespace.html#Mathlib.Linter.Style.Whitespace.mkWindow\"><span class=\"name\">Mathlib</span>.<span class=\"name\">Linter</span>.<span class=\"name\">Style</span>.<span class=\"name\">Whitespace</span>.<span class=\"name\">mkWindow</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">orig</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Data/String/Defs.html#String.Slice\">String.Slice</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">start </span><span class=\"fn\">ctx</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Nat\">Nat</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./Init/Data/String/Defs.html#String.Slice\">String.Slice</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"`mkWindow orig start ctx` extracts from `orig` a string that starts at the first\nnon-whitespace character before `start`, then expands to cover `ctx` more characters\nand continues still until the first non-whitespace character.\n\nIn essence, it extracts the substring of `orig` that begins at `start`, continues for `ctx`\ncharacters plus expands left and right until it encounters the first whitespace character,\nto avoid cutting into \"words\".\n\n*Note*. `start` is the number of characters *from the right* where our focus is!\n","docLink":"./Mathlib/Tactic/Linter/Whitespace.html#Mathlib.Linter.Style.Whitespace.mkWindow","kind":"def","line":291,"name":"Mathlib.Linter.Style.Whitespace.mkWindow","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/a3a10db0e9d66acbebf76c5e6a135066525ac900/Mathlib/Tactic/Linter/Whitespace.lean#L291-L306"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">opaque</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/Tactic/Linter/Whitespace.html#Mathlib.Linter.linter.style.whitespace.verbose\"><span class=\"name\">Mathlib</span>.<span class=\"name\">Linter</span>.<span class=\"name\">linter</span>.<span class=\"name\">style</span>.<span class=\"name\">whitespace</span>.<span class=\"name\">verbose</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Lean/Data/Options.html#Lean.Option\">Lean.Option</a> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Bool\">Bool</a></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"If the `linter.style.whitespace.verbose` option is `true`, the `whitespace` linter\nreports some helpful diagnostic information. ","docLink":"./Mathlib/Tactic/Linter/Whitespace.html#Mathlib.Linter.linter.style.whitespace.verbose","kind":"opaque","line":50,"name":"Mathlib.Linter.linter.style.whitespace.verbose","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/a3a10db0e9d66acbebf76c5e6a135066525ac900/Mathlib/Tactic/Linter/Whitespace.lean#L50-L55"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">opaque</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/Tactic/Linter/Whitespace.html#Mathlib.Linter.linter.style.commandStart\"><span class=\"name\">Mathlib</span>.<span class=\"name\">Linter</span>.<span class=\"name\">linter</span>.<span class=\"name\">style</span>.<span class=\"name\">commandStart</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Lean/Data/Options.html#Lean.Option\">Lean.Option</a> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Bool\">Bool</a></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Deprecated in favour of `linter.style.whitespace ","docLink":"./Mathlib/Tactic/Linter/Whitespace.html#Mathlib.Linter.linter.style.commandStart","kind":"opaque","line":43,"name":"Mathlib.Linter.linter.style.commandStart","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/a3a10db0e9d66acbebf76c5e6a135066525ac900/Mathlib/Tactic/Linter/Whitespace.lean#L43-L48"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span clas